### 6.4 Gain Calculation

#### Transconductance

gm = 2ID / Vov  
gm = (2 × 0.4165 mA) / 0.334  
gm = 2.49 mS  

---

#### Theoretical Gain

Av = −gm × RD  
Av = −(2.49×10⁻³ × 2160)  
Av = −5.38  

Convert to dB:

Av(dB) = 20 log10(5.38)  
Av(dB) ≈ 14.6 dB  

---

#### Simulated Gain

From AC plot: we got gain of each transistor as 2.29 so on further calculation


Vout = V(out1) - V(out2)

V(out1) = +2.29 × Vin  

V(out2) = −2.29 × Vin  

Vout = (+2.29 − (−2.29)) × Vin


Vout = 4.58 × Vin  

Vout/Vin = 4.58

Av =4.58 v/v

Av= 20 log(Av)

Av=20 log (4.58)

Av =13.217 db 


