## 8. Conclusion

- The measured gain of the amplifier is **2.28 V/V (7.16 dB)**.

- The **-3 dB bandwidth is 7.66 MHz**, which satisfies the theoretical condition:

- The calculated **Gain-Bandwidth Product (GBW) = 17.47 MHz**.

- The measured **Unity Gain Bandwidth (UGB) = 15.22 MHz**, which is close to GBW.

- This confirms that the amplifier approximately follows **single dominant pole behavior**, with slight deviation due to practical non-idealities.

